    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="735"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">895.01/7–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 735<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">July 21,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 167. 1. The President has received from <persName corresp="#p_RS2"
                        >Syngman Rhee</persName> a telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d735fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> requesting <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1">Stalin</persName> and the President to issue a
                    joint statement repudiating any secret agreement that might affect the
                    political, administrative and territorial integrity of Korea, and recognizing
                    “The Provisional Government of Korea”. The telegram requests opportunity for the
                    “Provisional Government” to collaborate in military operations against Japan and
                    gives undertaking to hold national election not later than one year after return
                    to Korea.</p>
                <p>2. Please make acknowledgment to <persName corresp="#p_RS2">Rhee</persName> in
                    such informal manner and in such terms as you may consider appropriate.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d735fn2">The Acting Secretary of State acknowledged the
                        receipt of <persName corresp="#p_RS2">Rhee</persName>’s telegram on July 24
                        (file No. 895.01/7–2145).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
